            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>brioche buns </strong>to a baking tray and put them in the oven for 5-6 min or until warmed through</p><p>Once warmed through, remove the buns from the oven and slice them in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>grated cheese </strong>and <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>mushrooms </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with<strong> </strong>a generous grind of<strong> black pepper </strong>and blitz until smooth</p><p>Shape the<strong> cheesy mushroom mixture</strong> into a patty[ies] for per person</p><p>Tip: Use <strong>flour</strong> on your hands if it's too sticky to handle and aim for the patties to be flat and wide (a little wider than the brioche buns if possible!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>mushroom patties</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until browned and crispy</p><p>Tip: Remember to handle gently as the patties may be fragile!</p><p>While the cheesy mushroom patties are cooking, roughly chop your <strong>dill</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>chopped dill</strong>, <strong>ketchup </strong>and your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong> in a small bowl – this is your<strong> burger sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper, then remove 1  <strong>outer leaf[ves] </strong>for per person and set aside, then cut the <strong>remaining lettuce </strong>into wedges</p><p>Drain the <strong>quick-pickled shallots</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1715.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fill the <strong>warm brioche halves</strong> with the <strong>lettuce</strong> <strong>leaves</strong>, <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>mushroom</strong> <strong>patties</strong>, <strong>burger</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and <strong>quick-pickled</strong> <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chips</strong>,<strong> lettuce wedges</strong> and any <strong>remaining burger sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> </strong>lettuce wedges with<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
